WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.000
Have you ever wondered what separates a good manager from a great one?

00:00:03.000 --> 00:00:09.000
It’s not just experience or qualifications—it’s the skills they bring to the table!

00:00:09.000 --> 00:00:15.000
Stick around as we break down the top 10 management skills every manager must master.

00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:21.000
...to lead teams effectively and achieve success, with examples to put them into action.

00:00:21.000 --> 00:00:24.000
So, grab your notepad and let's break this down!

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:29.000
Section 1: What Are Management Skills and Why Do They Matter?

00:00:29.000 --> 00:00:35.000
"Management is doing things right; leadership is doing the right things." — Peter Drucker

00:00:35.000 --> 00:00:39.000
Management skills help you organize, lead, and coordinate people and resources.

00:00:39.000 --> 00:00:44.000
They’re not just about being ‘the boss’ — they’re about building relationships and driving results.

00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:49.000
Think of them as the engine of a car. Without them, you’re going nowhere.

00:00:49.000 --> 00:00:55.000
Section 2: Essential Management Skills Every Manager Should Have

00:00:55.000 --> 00:01:04.000
1st. Human Skills: Understand, motivate, and manage individuals — the glue of a team.

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:14.000
Example: Address an underperformer’s issues and balance the workload for a high performer.

00:01:14.000 --> 00:01:21.000
Pro Tip: Regular 1:1s and team-building foster trust and collaboration.

00:01:21.000 --> 00:01:27.000
2nd. Communication Skills: The bridge to understanding.

00:01:27.000 --> 00:01:33.000
Clearly convey ideas, instructions, and feedback.

00:01:33.000 --> 00:01:42.000
Example: Pitch a campaign to execs and ensure the creative team understands the plan.

00:01:42.000 --> 00:01:46.000
Pro Tip: Active listening is as important as speaking clearly.

00:01:46.000 --> 00:01:52.000
3rd. Technical Skills: The foundation — know your tools and processes.

00:01:52.000 --> 00:02:00.000
Example: A marketing manager uses Google Analytics to guide strategy.

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:06.000
Pro Tip: Stay updated with industry trends to stay relevant.

00:02:06.000 --> 00:02:12.000
4th. Conceptual Skills: See the big picture and align actions with goals.

00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:20.000
Example: A product manager sees how a new feature impacts UX, sales, and development.

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:27.000
Pro Tip: Use SWOT analysis to sharpen your strategy.

00:02:27.000 --> 00:02:34.000
5th. Leadership Skills: Inspire and motivate your team to excel.

00:02:34.000 --> 00:02:43.000
Example: Satya Nadella revamped Microsoft’s culture by focusing on empathy.

00:02:43.000 --> 00:02:48.000
Pro Tip: Empathy connects great leaders with their teams.

00:02:48.000 --> 00:02:54.000
6th. Problem-Solving: Tackle challenges creatively and efficiently.

00:02:54.000 --> 00:03:06.000
Example: A logistics manager negotiates new vendors to handle supplier delays.

00:03:06.000 --> 00:03:11.000
Pro Tip: Define the problem before jumping to solutions.

00:03:11.000 --> 00:03:16.000
7th. Time Management: Prioritize tasks and manage time effectively.

00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:21.000
Example: An event planner schedules roles to run events smoothly.

00:03:21.000 --> 00:03:27.000
Pro Tip: Use to-do lists and time blocking.

00:03:27.000 --> 00:03:32.000
8th. Directing & Oversight: Guide and monitor teams.

00:03:32.000 --> 00:03:39.000
Example: A construction manager inspects sites to keep projects on track.

00:03:39.000 --> 00:03:46.000
Pro Tip: Set clear expectations and provide feedback.

00:03:46.000 --> 00:03:52.000
9th. Adaptability: Thrive through change.

00:03:52.000 --> 00:03:59.000
Example: A restaurant owner pivots to online delivery during the pandemic.

00:03:59.000 --> 00:04:05.000
Pro Tip: Stay open-minded and embrace learning.

00:04:05.000 --> 00:04:11.000
10th. Decision-Making: Analyze, diagnose, and choose wisely.

00:04:11.000 --> 00:04:19.000
Example: A retail manager fixes poor inventory placement to boost sales.

00:04:19.000 --> 00:04:24.000
Pro Tip: Combine data and instinct for balanced decisions.

00:04:24.000 --> 00:04:31.000
Section 3: How to Develop Management Skills

00:04:31.000 --> 00:04:39.000
1. Education: Enroll in workshops and online courses like Coursera.

00:04:39.000 --> 00:04:46.000
2. Experience: Volunteer for leadership roles big and small.

00:04:46.000 --> 00:04:52.000
3. Mentorship: Shadow experienced managers.

00:04:52.000 --> 00:04:58.000
4. Feedback: Seek and apply feedback from peers and teams.

00:04:58.000 --> 00:05:06.000
5. Mindfulness: Use each challenge to refine your skills and stay calm.

00:05:06.000 --> 00:05:14.000
